[2
Date: Fri, 23 Jul 1999 15:51:50 -0400
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>

Interfax reported today that the number of deaths in the Stavropol Region is
4. Also from Interfax: total of 66 cases in Rostov region, 6 deaths, 24
still in hospital of whom 8 are in serious condition and 1 in critical
condition.
BBC quoting Itar-Tass repeats that number of cases in Rostov is 90, 6 dead,
29 discharged from hospital with 10 to be discharged shortly. But the BBC
report contradicts previous reports of no new cases: it says 2 patients
with preliminary diagnosis of the disease were admitted to hospital in the
past 2 days. [Possible interpretation: no new confirmed cases, but 2
possible positives. The hospitalized patients include 3 medical workers,
including one anesthesist who is in grave condition.
